    {"repo": "servo--be6a2f99", "path": "Cargo.toml"},
    {"repo": "servo--be6a2f99", "path": "tests/unit/style/Cargo.toml"},
    {"repo": "rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs"},
    {"repo": "rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs"},
    {"repo": "rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/Cargo.toml"}
  ],
  "symbols": [
    {"repo": "rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs", "symbol": "BridgeConfig"},
    {"repo": "rust--01f6ddf7", "path": "library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs", "symbol": "with_api"}
  ],
  "text": "1. SERVO/SERVO style and selectors crates: In the servo--be6a2f99 snapshot, the `components/style/` and `components/selectors/` directories do NOT exist. Those crates were extracted into the separate `servo/stylo` repository. The root `Cargo.toml` (servo--be6a2f99/Cargo.toml) references them as git dependencies: `selectors = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }` and `stylo = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`. The Cargo.lock shows the `selectors` crate (v0.35.0) depends on: bitflags, cssparser, derive_more, log, new_debug_unreachable, phf, phf_codegen, precomputed-hash, rustc-hash, servo_arc, smallvec, to_shmem, to_shmem_derive. The `stylo` (style) crate (v0.11.0) depends on: app_units, arrayvec, atomic_refcell, bitflags, byteorder, cssparser, derive_more, encoding_rs, euclid, icu_segmenter, indexmap, itertools, itoa, log, malloc_size_of_derive, mime, new_debug_unreachable, num-derive, num-integer, num-traits, num_cpus, parking_lot, precomputed-hash, rayon, rayon-core, rustc-hash, selectors, serde, servo_arc, smallbitvec, smallvec, static_assertions, string_cache, stylo_atoms, stylo_config, stylo_derive, stylo_dom, stylo_malloc_size_of, stylo_static_prefs, stylo_traits, thin-vec, to_shmem, to_shmem_derive, uluru, url, void, walkdir, web_atoms. The only local style-related test is at `tests/unit/style/Cargo.toml` (crate name `style_tests`). There is no `components/style/lib.rs` in this snapshot.\n\n2. RUST-LANG/RUST selectors dependency: No crate under `compiler/` or `library/` in rust--01f6ddf7 depends on or references Servo's `selectors` crate. There are no mentions of `selectors`, `servo`, or `stylo` in any Cargo.toml file within the rust-lang/rust repository.\n\n3. PROC_MACRO BRIDGE: The file that defines the `proc_macro` bridge is `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs` in rust--01f6ddf7. This file defines the internal interface (via the `with_api!` macro and `BridgeConfig` struct) for communicating between a proc_macro client (a proc macro crate or Servo build script) and a proc_macro server (the compiler front-end). The bridge uses C ABI buffers and unique integer handles to allow safe interfacing between different compiler versions. The `BridgeConfig` struct carries the input buffer and dispatch closure. The bridge is exposed from `library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs` as `pub mod bridge`."
}

